<HEADLINE> Mariners' Shortstop Carlos Guillen Hurt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) - Seattle Mariners rookie shortstop Carlos Guillen  
was helped off the field in the third inning Saturday, after 
spraining his right knee in a home plate collision with Oakland's 
Tony Phillips. 
</P>
<P>
	Guillen, 23, was taken for precautionary X-rays after Charles  
Gipson replaced him. Guillen sustained a season-ending injury to 
his left knee last Sept. 17 at Oakland. 
</P>
<P>
	Guillen became Seattle's second injured shortstop. All-Star Alex  
Rodriguez is sidelined 4-6 weeks following surgery on his left 
knee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
