<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Evel Knievel Admitted to Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Evel Knievel, admitted to a hospital amid  
concerns that his body was rejecting his new liver, was released 
after doctors determined he was battling hepatitis. 
</P>
<P>
	The 60-year-old former daredevil had a lifesaving liver  
transplant two months ago. He said he had been waiting for a new 
liver to replace one wracked by hepatitis C he says was caused by 
years of blood transfusions. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think my body is rejecting the liver or my hepatitis C is  
coming back and overtaking my liver,'' Knievel said earlier Friday 
from his bed at Sunrise Hospital and Medical Center. ``I've been 
feeling weak and dizzy and tired.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hospital spokeswoman Ann Lynch said doctors determined the liver  
had not been rejected but Knievel's body was ``just being attacked 
by hepatitis.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He was released from the hospital late in the day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
