<DOCNO> APW19990410.0044 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-10 01:51:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Zito To Test 2nd String at the Wood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Trainer Nick Zito is looking for a few more  
Kentucky Derby horses in today's $600,000 Wood Memorial. 
</P>
<P>
	Already, Zito's Stephen Got Even is headed to Churchill Downs  
off his victory in the GalleryFurniture.com Stakes at Turfway Park 
on March 27. 
</P>
<P>
	He's also penciled in Wondertross, the early favorite for  
today's Blue Grass Stakes at Keeneland, for the May 1 Derby. 
</P>
<P>
	In the Wood, Zito hopes his second-stringers Adonis and The  
Groom Is Red can prove themselves worthy of a trip to Churchill 
Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	``These are two good horses,'' said Zito, a two-time Derby  
winner with Strike the Gold in 1991 and Go for Gin in 1994. ``They 
worked great the other day and I think you're going to see their 
best efforts.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Adonis, a powerfully built son of Kris S., was a wide sixth in  
the Florida Derby after having won his previous two races. Adonis, 
the 4-1 second choice behind favored Badge, will be ridden by Jorge 
Chavez. The colt will wear blinkers for the first time. 
</P>
<P>
	The Groom Is Red, a 15-1 shot, is the only Grade I winner in the  
11-horse field for the 1 1/8-mile Wood (ABC-TV, post time 5:42 p.m. 
EDT). But the Rick Pitino-owned colt hasn't won as a 3-year-old. In 
his last two races, The Groom Is Red was sixth in the 
GalleryFurniture.com, and seventh on the Fountain of Youth on Feb. 
28. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think The Groom Is Red has finally come around,'' Zito said.  
``As for Adonis, all you have to do was look at the trip he had in 
the Florida Derby and you know he's a better horse than what he 
showed.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Badge, trained by retired fireman John Aquilino, won the Gotham  
by 7 1/2 lengths in a speedy time of 1:34 3-5 for the mile. The son of 
Air Forbes Won has won four of his last five races. 
</P>
<P>
	The field, from the rail out, is: Badge (3-1, Shaun Bridgmohan);  
Karly's Harley (8-1, Edgar Prado); Bugatti (15-1, Robbie Davis); 
Adonis (4-1, Jorge Chavez); Cliquot (9-2, Rene Douglas); The Groom 
is Red (15-1, Craig Perret); David (12-1, Aaron Gryder); Robin 
Goodfellow (20-1, Joe Bravo); Machine To Tower (20-1, Cornelio 
Velasquez); Best of Luck (12-1, Jean-Luc Samyn), and Swamp (6-1, 
Richard Migliore). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
