<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Actress Judd Works for Peace Corps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Ashley Judd took a break from the glamor of  
movie stardom to live out her longtime dream to become a Peace 
Corps volunteer. 
</P>
<P>
	The actress with credits including ``Heat'' and ``Kiss the  
Girls'' spent a week in a remote Amazon jungle village in Suriname, 
where she lived without electricity and running water. 
</P>
<P>
	``I woke up once during the night to go to the bathroom,'' Judd  
says in the May issue of Marie Claire magazine. ``Using facilities 
outside was not an uncomfortable adjustment for me. I grew up using 
an outhouse whenever I visited my great aunt and uncle on their 
farm.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Hollywood beauty enjoyed her time among the friendly  
residents of Asawai on the banks of the piranha-filled Saramacca 
River, and didn't have too many difficulties with local wildlife. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm not intimidated by nature and I found nothing fearsome,  
despite the jungle's reputation,'' she said. ``The only encounter I 
had was being chased back to the hut by a mosquito which seemed to 
be the size of my hand.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
