<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Internet Execs To Field Questions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- As many as 45,000 people are expected to go  
online Wednesday for a daylong conference call that will give 
ordinary investors access to top Internet executives. 
</P>
<P>
	Chief executive officers and chief financial officers from  
Internet companies like Excite Inc. and Yahoo! Inc. will take part 
in the daylong call, scheduled for 8 a.m. to 8 p.m. EDT. 
</P>
<P>
	Vcall Corp., a Philadelphia-based provider of Internet  
conference calls, will waive its usual fee and won't require a 
password for the event. 
</P>
<P>
	Joe Besecker, the company's founder, said he envisioned  
``VcallApolooza'' as a vehicle for individual investors to quiz the 
leaders of the Internet companies that have become hot properties 
in the ongoing bull market. 
</P>
<P>
	``It'll level the playing field by allowing individuals to ask  
questions they'd never get to ask,'' he said Friday. Individual 
investors are rarely invited to take part in analyst meetings or 
conference calls. 
</P>
<P>
	The executives taking part in Wednesday's virtual conference  
call will make speeches or hold discussions with their counterparts 
over real-time audio and video feeds. Listeners may send questions 
via e-mail. 
</P>
<P>
	Besecker said he expects people to come and go throughout the  
day, logging in only for the speakers that most interest them. 
</P>
<P>
	Vcall also hopes to use the conference call as a marketing tool  
to attract future paying listeners, advertisers and clients. The 
company, founded in 1997, broadcasts corporate conference calls 
over the Internet for a fee so that investors can listen in. 
</P>
<P>
	To date, Vcall's largest audience has been about 20,000 people,  
who listened in to a conference call with Dell Computer Corp. 
Besecker said Vcall's technology can easily handle wider audiences, 
and he doesn't expect technical snares. 
</P>
<P>
	The conference call is accessible through Vcall's Web site, at  
www.vcall.com. 

</P>
</TEXT>
