<HEADLINE> Nissan Sought Iacocca To Pitch Cars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Lee Iacocca, a pitchman for Nissan cars?  
</P>
<P>
	A Nissan executive says he tried unsuccessfully to get the  
former Chrysler Corp. chairman to appear in a series of ads for the 
Japanese automaker. 
</P>
<P>
	``The question was, how could we cut through the clutter with TV  
ads last December?'' Mike Seergy, vice president and general 
manager of Nissan's U.S. operations, told Friday's Detroit News. 
``It just popped in my head that someone who personified 
`turnaround' was Iacocca.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Iacocca helped Chrysler emerge from a downward spiral in the  
1970s to a resurgence in the 80s, and had been critical of Japanese 
car makers. 
</P>
<P>
	Seergy hoped to battle a decline in sales and image by featuring  
ads with Iacocca saying, ``Nissan makes great cars.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Plans for a series of ads were made, but came undone after  
Iacocca said he wanted to look into ``cross-marketing deals'' 
involving his electric bicycle venture, the News reported. 
</P>
<P>
	Iacocca has downplayed his dealings with Nissan in the past, the  
paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
