<HEADLINE> Islanders Sign Hobey Baker Winner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	UNIONDALE, N.Y. (AP) -- Jason Krog, winner of the Hobey Baker  
award as college hockey's best player, has signed a multiyear 
contract with the New York Islanders. 
</P>
<P>
	Krog scored 94 goals and had 144 assists in 151 games at the  
University of New Hampshire, runner-up to Maine in the NCAA hockey 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	He had 20 goals and 33 assists in Hockey East this year,  
becoming the first player since Paul Kariya, now with the Anaheim 
Mighty Ducks, to score more than 50 points in league play. 
</P>
<P>
	Financial details of the contract were not disclosed.  
</P>
