<HEADLINE> INS Arrests 18-Foreign-Born Felons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- U.S. Immigration and Naturalization  
officials arrested 18 foreign-born felons convicted of crimes 
including murder, fraud and money laundering. 
</P>
<P>
	Three months ago the agency began an operation in four Florida  
cities targeting legal resident aliens who have been convicted of 
what the INS describes as aggravated felonies. 
</P>
<P>
	Each of the felons will be held in custody until they are  
deported or their case is heard by an immigration judge. The felons 
were convicted in the United States, served their sentences and had 
been released. 
</P>
<P>
	Those arrested Friday were from 14 countries: Belgium, Pakistan,  
Phillippines, Colombia, Guadeloupe, Bahamas, India, Trinidad, 
Dominican Republic, Ecuador, Jamaica, Mexico, Canada and Venezuela. 
</P>
<P>
	The operation has been conducted in Orlando, Casselberry, DeLand  
and Daytona Beach. 
</P>
