<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jeweler Tiffany Sues Nude Bar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) -- Tiffany &AMP; Co. is suing a nude-bar  
namesake. 
</P>
<P>
	The New York City-based diamond, silver and luxury goods company  
filed a trademark infringement lawsuit in federal court Friday 
against the operators of Tiffany's, a soon-to-open nude juice bar. 
</P>
<P>
	``Tiffany's represents quality and style, not what these people  
are trying to sell,'' a lawyer for the company, Jim Swire, said in 
Saturday's Rochester Democrat and Chronicle. 
</P>
<P>
	The company sent a letter weeks ago protesting the bar's name  
but got no response, he said. Federal law forbids a blurring, 
tarnishing or whittling away of the distinctiveness of a famous 
trademark. 
</P>
<P>
	The bar's owners won $10,000 in damages last month from the city  
of Rochester, which conceded that it improperly thwarted them from 
opening the bar earlier this year. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
