<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rapids 4, Fusion 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Wolde Harris scored two goals and Anders Limpar  
had two assists to lead the Colorado Rapids to a 4-1 victory over 
the Miami Fusion in the MLS on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Midfielder Ross Paule of Colorado (1-2) opened the scoring in  
the 48th minute when he sent a cross into the box and the ball 
bounced off Fusion defender Jay Heaps and into the net. 
</P>
<P>
	Harris scored his first goal a minute later on a through ball  
from Paule. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami (1-3) scored in the 54th minute on Diego Serna's goal with  
assists from Roberto Gaucho and Nelson Vargas. 
</P>
<P>
	Dely Valdes scored on Limpar's corner kick in the 62nd minute  
and Harris notched his second goal by redirecting a shot by Marcelo 
Balboa after another corner kick by Limpar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
