<HEADLINE> Burn 1, Fire 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Matt Jordan had six saves and the Dallas Burn  
extended its shutout streak to a team-record 328 minutes with a 1-0 
shootout victory over the Chicago Fire on Saturday night, ruining 
the home opener for the defending MLS Cup champions. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas (2-1) was outshot 11-6 and the Fire (3-1) could not score  
despite playing with a man advantage for the final 28 minutes. 
Dallas defender Eric Dade was sent off in the 62nd minute following 
a tackle from behind on Chicago's Ante Razov. 
</P>
<P>
	In the shootout, Brian Haynes and Richard Farrer scored in the  
first two frames for the Burn, while Ted Eck clinched it with a 
goal in the fifth frame. Only Jesse Marsch converted for the Fire 
in Chicago's four attempts. 
</P>
<P>
	Despite chilly, wet weather, a crowd of 27,311 was on hand at  
Soldier Field for a pregame ceremony honoring the 1998 MLS champs. 
The MLS said it was the largest crowd so far this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
