<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Piece of Plane Lands in Mass. Yard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SPRINGFIELD, Mass. (AP) -- A 16-foot flap fell off a military  
plane's wing Saturday and into a suburban backyard, narrowly 
missing a couple who were doing outdoor chores. 
</P>
<P>
	John Stocks was raking his yard when he saw the flap falling  
about 50 feet above him, and called out to his wife, Amy. She and 
the dog, who were standing near the garage, got out of the way. 
</P>
<P>
	The flap panel, from a C-5A transport plane, crushed a  
clothesline pole and tore into the Stocks' lawn. It came to rest 
inches from a bulkhead leading to their basement. 
</P>
<P>
	Smaller bits of debris landed near two other area homes.  
</P>
<P>
	The plane, from Westover Air Reserve Base, was on a routine  
training mission. It landed safely, base officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	Tech. Sgt. William Pope said it was unclear what caused the flap  
to break off the plane. Officials retrieved the plane flap panel, 
and the incident remained under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
