<HEADLINE> United 3, Revolution 2, SO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- Defender Carlos Llamosa scored on the  
ninth shot of the shootout and D.C. United remained unbeaten with a 
3-2 victory over the New England Revolution on Saturday in Major 
League Soccer. 
</P>
<P>
	In the shootout, the United's Marco Etcheverry, Geoff Aunger and  
Ben Olsen scored on the first, seventh and eighth shots. New 
England's Joe-Max Moore, Jair and Dan Calichman matched those 
goals. 
</P>
<P>
	But then Llamosa placed the ball under goalkeeper Walter Zenga  
to make it 4-3, and the Revolution's Ted Chronopolous misfired high 
and wide to the left on the next shot. 
</P>
<P>
	United (3-0) took a 1-0 lead when Aunger scored on a header with  
just nine seconds remaining in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
	Moore made it 1-1 with his second goal of the season on a direct  
kick at 49:32. At 72:57, Roy Lassiter converted a cross from the 
right wing by Olsen for his fourth goal of the season and a 2-1 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
	But with 7:39 remaining in regulation, New England forward  
Johnny Torres scored from the right wing, beating goalkeeper Tom 
Presthus to the far left post. 
</P>
