<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Adonis Is Golden in Wood Memorial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Trainer Nick Zito looks like he has himself  
another Kentucky Derby starter. 
</P>
<P>
	Adonis caught the leaders at the top of the stretch and pulled  
away just outside the eighth pole for a two-length victory in 
Saturday's $600,000 Wood Memorial at Aqueduct. 
</P>
<P>
	Zito, a two-time Derby winner with Strike the Gold and Go for  
Gin, already has Stephen Got Even set for the May 1 Derby and said 
he'll probably take Wondertross, too, despite a sixth-place finish 
in the Blue Grass Stakes run earlier in the day at Keeneland. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're happy with Adonis, and disappointed with Wondertross,''  
Zito said from Keeneland after listening to the live call of the 
Wood. 
</P>
<P>
	Adonis, wearing blinkers for the first time at the suggestion of  
jockey Jorge Chavez, won for the third time in his last four races. 
In his previous race, Adonis was sixth in the Florida Derby but had 
a poor trip after being forced outside. 
</P>
<P>
	Adonis, owned by Ernie Paragallo, covered 1 1/8 miles in 1:47 3-5,  
2-5 of second off the stakes record. Adonis finished two lengths 
ahead of Best of Luck, with Cliquot third, another 1 3/4 lengths back. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner returned $8.40, $5.10 and $3.90. Best of Luck,  
trained by Hall of Famer Allen Jerkens, paid $8.80 and $5.60, and 
Cliquot, a California shipper, returned $5 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Badge, the 2-1 favorite of the crowd of 15,104, was fourth,  
followed by The Groom Is Red, Swamp, Machine To Tower, David, 
Karley's Harley, Bugatti and Robin Goodfellow. 
</P>
<P>
	Zito also trains The Groom Is Red for Boston Celtics president  
and coach Rick Pitino. 
</P>
<P>
	Before the Wood, Zito said he expected a ``big, big  
performance.'' And he got it from the lightly raced colt, who has 
run just six races. 
</P>
<P>
	``I hope we're there again,'' Zito said. ``Jorge suggested that  
we put blinkers on him, he was not paying attention and not 
concentrating. He was absolutely right. This combination worked. 
Jorge is a terrific rider. I think he's going to get his due now.'' 
</P>
<P>
	For Zito, the win was his second in the Wood, one of the final  
major prep races for the Derby. He won with Thirty Six Red in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
	On the undercard, Perfect Score held off Royal Ruby by a head to  
win the $100,000 Bayshore for 3-year-olds, covering seven furlongs 
in 1:23. The winner returned $9.10, 4.90 and $3.30. 
</P>
<P>
	Kelly Kip, the 2-5 favorite, broke his own track record for six  
furlongs in winning the $100,000 Bold Ruler Stakes by 2 1/2 lengths 
over Artax. Kelly Kip's time of 1:07 2-5 clipped 1-5 of a second 
off the mark he set on April 11, 1998. The winner paid $2.90, $2.30 
and $2.10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
